    "caption": "A flash of electric blue that's gone before you can blink.",
    "shortDescription": "Kingfishers are so brightly colored they look almost fake — electric blue on top, rusty orange underneath. They hunt by perching over a stream, watching the water with their head tilted to correct for light refraction, then diving in bill-first to catch a fish they spotted before it could react. Fun fact: Kingfishers beat a caught fish against a branch to stun it and flip it head-first so it slides down smoothly."
